name: Cibo
directions: In back behind Cibo, Townsends and other shops. They all share a back hallway.

name: Banana Cafe
directions: Left from the entrance, close to the front.

name: Kenmore Branch Library
directions: Past the circulation desk, behind the DVDs

name: BreadHive Bakery
directions: one solo restroom marked neutral
comment: no worries, just use it! sincerely, the proprietors

name: Fantom Comics
directions: Second door to the left when you walk into the store.
comment: They hope that you'll purchase something, but they won't hassle you about it. The staff is super friendly and welcoming, and hosts a Queer Book Club every month if you want to come and chat with other folks ðŸ˜Š

name: Vinh Loi Tofu
directions: At the back of the restaurant
comment: You need to be a customer to use the restroom. They have a fridge you can buy drinks from

name: Hilton Columbus Downtown
directions: First floor lobby level, from the front door, take a left to the end of the hallway, then take a right to the end of that hallway past the meeting rooms. There is a companion care single restroom before the gendered communal restrooms.
comment: It's a little hidden, way back in the far corner of the hotel. Follow the directions and you will see it on your right. You do not have to be a guest to use our restrooms!

name: Indiana Legal Services
directions: Second floor. There's an elevator. Immediate left. Right down the  hall. Then left. The bathrooms will be on the left.
comment: They're gendered but the staff at ILS are mostly knowledgeable on trans issues and won't question you. It's usually not very busy and there are plenty of other organizations.

name: Kwik Trip
comment: There is one neutral single stall bathroom, plus gendered bathrooms. Not sure if the gendered bathrooms are single or multi stall.

name: 711 at Temple University
directions: In the very back of the store behind the slurpees.
comment: You can use the bathroom and not buy anything.

name: Exiles Bar
directions: First floor, past bar in back

name: Saxby's in Temple University
directions: In the back of the coffeeshop
comment: You can probably just walk in and use the bathroom without buying a coffee

name: Cheesie's Pub & Grub
directions: If you go to the east side of the restaurant passed the bar it is straight back.
comment: I'm an employee and we let people come in to use the restroom often, as long as it's not someone who we know has made a huge mess or something before.

name: UCLA EPSS
directions: First floor, in small hallway on the western side of the building, most of the way drown the hall. Has a triangle on the door.
comment: Public universities are open to the public during business hours but the first floor door is usually open.

name: The Center for Arts at the Armory
directions: In the cafe

name: Starbuck
directions: To the right when you come in, two single person handicap gender neutral bathrooms

name: St. Marys Hospital
directions: There are several all gender restrooms on the main level/public areas as well as other floors of the hospital.
comment: Most areas on the main floor level are accessible by the public unless marked otherwise.

name: Cold Stone Creamery
comment: Have to be a paying customer

name: Cold Stone Creamery
comment: Have to be a paying customer

name: Michaels Beaverton
directions: Far left corner of the store
comment: For customers but browse a bit :)

name: Unitarian Universalist Church of Boulder
directions: Walk forward to the end of the hall, turn right through the double doors. Bathroom on the left.
comment: Inconsistent hours during the week, definitely open Sunday mornings.

name: Target
directions: Inside front entrance, on the right hand side. "Family" restroom. Single toilet. Locking door.

name: penfield high school
directions: first floor, by the side entrance near the community center.
comment: must be a student or visitor

name: eden-a vegan cafe
directions: Down the hallway past our cafe's dining room, single gender neutral restroom on the right.
comment: It's best to be a customer, but of course if someone needs a safe space our entire restaurant is one for you.

name: Comic Envy
directions: Back corner, blue door painted like a Police Box.
comment: Please feel free to ask if you need a safe space, staff is LGBT+ and very welcoming!

name: Barnes and Noble
directions: 2nd floor on the right

name: Govinda's Vegetarian Restaurant
comment: Must be a customer to use; Govinda's is a safe space and local favorite for the LGBTQ+ community.

name: Central Ohio Technical College
directions: North classroom building, Between the dorms and the Main circle of buildings. There are 4 Single stall bathrooms.

name: Publix
directions: Family type restroom near the pharmacy and other restrooms.
comment: Clean, nice, busy store with generally kind employees

name: planet Puzza
directions: Hall on the right all the way back.

name: Blake Hall
directions: ground floor, take a left from main lobby and it's right across from the computer lab
comment: building locks after 6 pm on weekdays and all day on weekends.  you will need a valid student ID at that point

name: Little Deli & Pizzeria
directions: In the kitchen, to the right

name: Aldrich Memorial Nursery School
directions: Side hallway across from Room 3
comment: Check in and get a visitors badge at the front desk first

name: Stewart's Gas Station
directions: In the store around the counter past the second register, by the lotto tickets

name: Starbucks - Oak Park
directions: Located towards the back of the store
comment: 2 single person bathrooms marked "Restroom". It is suggested you order something.

name: kohls
directions: Located toward the right side back of the store. Past the kids clothing and to the right of customer service.

name: Staples
directions: On the west side of store, down a hallway.
comment: Gender-segregated washrooms, but trans-positive staff and management.

name: Shawnee Library
directions: Main floor, ask for key at front desk.
comment: A couple queer employees, LGBTQ safe space sign poster.

name: Walmart
directions: Located in the back of the store, between the toys and video games. Tucked back across from the online order pick up counter, between the gendered restrooms.
comment: No merchandise in the bathrooms.

name: Golden Brown Bakery
comment: It would be good manners to buy a cookie or a cup of coffee before using it.

name: DePaul Campus Building, Arts & Letters Hall
directions: go all the way to the back, and turn left. the stall should be right in between the male and female washrooms.
comment: this is a campus, but this is also an accepting and safe place. nobody will question why you're there, they will simply assume that you are a student.

name: Safeway
directions: Back of the store just past the right of the bakery

name: Safeway
directions: Back of the store just past the right of the bakery

name: Fair Trade Cafe
directions: To the left of the counter. Two gender neutral bathrooms

name: ergAdoozy
directions: When you first walk in, there's a hallway right before the play area and it's down the hall a bit.
comment: Have to be there with a younger child, children twelve and under are $3.

name: Mad Hanna
comment: It's a bar, two seperat single stall rooms. Both are unisex

name: Anthony's IV Pizza and Pasta
directions: 2 single gendered bathrooms in the back. Owner often tell customers of any gender to use either if one is occupied.
comment: Prefer paying customers but not mandatory

name: Anthony's IV Pizza and Pasta
directions: 2 single gendered bathrooms in the back. Owner often tell customers of any gender to use either if one is occupied.
comment: Prefer paying customers but not mandatory

name: Yo Wild
comment: Small yogurt shop, restroom is in the back.

name: Home Depot
directions: Back of the store in the lights section.

name: Macy's Starbucks
street: Corner of Northern and Community Dr.

name: Maria's Mexican restaurant
directions: Enter, turn right then left and heads toward the back of the restaurant. Signs indicate where it is
comment: Pretend you're there to see someone or ask to be put on the waiting list while you use the loo

name: Maria's Mexican restaurant
directions: Enter, turn right then left and heads toward the back of the restaurant. Signs indicate where it is
comment: Pretend you're there to see someone or ask to be put on the waiting list while you use the loo

name: Alma college
directions: A lot of the buildings have "safe spots" for all/gender.
comment: You usually have to be a student or there for an event, but I mean..If you need to use the bathroom, I'm sure they won't question too much.

name: Vine Congregational UCC Church
directions: Down stairs to the left and upstairs by the offices

name: Ramen Takumi
street: northeast corner of Washington Square Park
directions: All the way back and to the left.
comment: You have to be a customer. Accessible (largish room, metal bars behind & to left side of toilet) but pathway back may be a little narrow for a wheelchair.

name: The Bay Center
directions: Go into the mall, down to the lowest floor. Follow signs to bathroom from large courtyard area with giant compass on the floor. Family/accessible bathroom is behind large door opened with button located beside it
comment: You must open the door with a big red button and it opens and closes very slowly

name: Kohls
directions: Back of store, family restroom

name: Subway
directions: Right of entrance
comment: Being customer prob helps. Doors have 4-digit punch code, recently Mens was 5317 but often is unlatched so you don't need to bother them for the code.

name: Walmart
directions: Back of store

name: Kingâ€™s College Library, Kings/Dalhousie Campus
comment: Open to the public

name: Rowe Building, Dalhousie University
directions: Eight gender-neutral washrooms, two on each of floors two through five in the East Wing beside rooms 2141, 3141, 4141, and 5141.
comment: Ignore the signage for the male/female washrooms on all floors.

name: Killam Library, Dalhousie University
directions: Second floor between the male and female washrooms
comment: Open to the public

name: Rebecca Cohn Arts Centre, Dalhousie University
directions: Basement, off the Sculpture Court - go past the elevator and to the left.

name: GameKnight Games and Cool Stuff
directions: Red door about 20 feet in on the left.

name: Safeway Manoa Marketplace
directions: At the end of aisle 10

name: Strath Haven High School
directions: Third floor, near the physical therapy office and the pool, small hallway on the left
comment: Unfortunately because it's a school, you can only use it if you're a student/parent/staff member at Strath Haven or you're visiting there for some reason (sports, music, something)

name: Round Spring Ranger Station
directions: Ranger Station at entrance to Campground, once inside down the hallway to the left.

name: La Taza
directions: Immediately to the left upon entering.  Small single-stall.
comment: It's a coffee shop/ restaurant, you should probably plan on getting a coffee or iced tea or something.

name: Downing Student Union
directions: Basement floor, between gendered restrooms

name: St Francis Hospital
directions: 1st floor across from the green elevators. 3rd floor down the hall from the green elevators
comment: The ones across on the first floor are very small, about the size of a closet. There are also several single stalls along various hallways of the hospital.

name: Harvard Divinity School
directions: One specifically gender neutral per floor of Divinity Hall, next to a gendered multi-stall bathroom.

name: Marshalls,Poughkeepsie Plaza Mall
directions: Restroom in middle of left side wall facing in as you enter

name: Polaris ELS
directions: Just past the office, you may have to sign in
comment: The school had a trans staff member and is super accepting.

name: Whole Foods Market
directions: At the front of the store, to the far right as you enter, are two 'family-style' single restrooms.  Handicap accessible and diaper changing station.

name: Harvard Divinity School
directions: Andover Hall basement and 2nd floor
comment: Anyone would be happy to show you the bathroom! It's a private school but anyone can walk in and shouldn't be an issue. 2nd floor is a single un-gendered stall, basement is many single stalls, some gendered but no one pays attention to the genders listed

name: St Francis Hospital
directions: Third floor down the hallway from the dental clinic
comment: There are two in this hallway - one halfway and one at the very end.

name: Papa johns pizza
directions: Two restrooms, one next to front door, wheelchair accessible. The other at back of eating area, non accessible.
comment: Staff don't mind if you just come in for the restroom.
